## 📝 Final Observations & Comparison

### Changes Applied:
- **Table Name Conflict Fixed**: [MeaningSynonym](file:///d:/Code/Github-Code/EnglishApp/EnglishApp-backend-springboot/learning-service/src/main/java/com/tqt/englishApp/entity/MeaningSynonym.java#7-28) now correctly maps to `@Table(name = "meaning_synonym")`.
- **Lombok Standardized**: Almost all entities now use `@Data`, which provides getters, setters, `equals`, `hashCode`, and `toString` in one annotation.
- **New Field Added**: [Vocabulary](file:///d:/Code/Github-Code/EnglishApp/EnglishApp-backend-springboot/learning-service/src/main/java/com/tqt/englishApp/entity/Vocabulary.java#9-32) now has a `level` field (e.g., A1, B2, C1), which is excellent for filtering content by difficulty.

### ⚠️ A Small Note on `@Data`:
> [!NOTE]
> Since you are now using `@Data` on all entities, be mindful if you encounter `StackOverflowError` or performance issues with large object graphs (especially with `ManyToMany` circular references like `Vocabulary <-> SubTopic`). 
> If that happens, you might need to exclude the relationship fields from `toString` and `hashCode/equals` using `@ToString.Exclude` and `@EqualsAndHashCode.Exclude`.

### 🌟 Conclusion
The entity layer is now very clean and robust. The relationships are clear, auditing fields are in place (though still a mix of `LocalDate` and `LocalDateTime`, which is acceptable if intended), and the table mapping bug is gone.

**The current structure is ready for the Service and Repository layers.**
